                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-15T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your October 2, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>Your understanding as to suspension of indemnity payments is correct. If other
                    co-belligerent governments agree to proposed international tariff commission
                    this Government will appoint Commissioners with the understanding that the
                    revised tariff before it could become effective should presumably be
                    incorporated into a new treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
